# TunePath — Cursor Rules
# These rules apply to every prompt in this project. Read them fully before generating any code.

## Project Overview
TunePath is a cross-platform music learning app (iOS + Android, future Android TV).
It is built with Expo (React Native), FastAPI (Python), PostgreSQL, and Cloudflare R2.
The app teaches musical instruments using a Netflix-style model: standalone lessons and structured courses.

## Tech Stack
- Mobile: Expo SDK with Expo Router (file-based routing) — TypeScript throughout
- Backend: FastAPI (Python 3.11+)
- Database: PostgreSQL — single source of truth for all relational data
- Media storage: Cloudflare R2 — stores video, audio, thumbnails, notation.json only
- Auth: Clerk (@clerk/clerk-expo on mobile, clerk JWT verification on FastAPI)
- State management: Zustand (introduce only when a screen needs cross-screen state)
- Caching: Redis (backend only, for course/lesson list endpoints)
- Styling: StyleSheet from React Native (no NativeWind, no styled-components)

## Folder Structure — MUST follow this exactly

```
app/                          # Expo Router screens only — no logic here
  (tabs)/
    home.tsx
    practice.tsx
    progress.tsx
    profile.tsx
  (auth)/
    login.tsx
    onboarding.tsx
  course/[id].tsx
  lesson/[id].tsx              # Shell only — loads instrument plugin
  select/
    instrument.tsx
    level.tsx
  tutor/
    dashboard.tsx
    upload.tsx
    contributors.tsx
  admin/
    tutor-applications.tsx
    review-queue.tsx

instruments/                  # One folder per instrument — self-contained plugins
  harmonium/
    index.ts                  # Exports HarmoniumPlugin satisfying InstrumentPlugin interface
    HarmoniumPlayer.tsx
    SargamGrid.tsx
    StaffNotation.tsx
    BpmController.tsx
    GuidedPractice.tsx
    hooks/
      useSargam.ts
      useGuidedPractice.ts
    utils/
      notation.ts
      bpm.ts
    types/
      sargam.ts
  guitar/
    index.ts
    GuitarPlayer.tsx
  piano/
    index.ts
    PianoPlayer.tsx

src/
  registry/
    instrumentRegistry.ts     # Maps slug → plugin. One line per instrument.
    types.ts                  # InstrumentPlugin interface contract
  components/
    common/                   # Generic UI atoms — no instrument logic
      LoadingState.tsx
      ErrorState.tsx
      EmptyState.tsx
      SectionHeader.tsx
      ProgressBadge.tsx
    lesson/
      VideoPlayer.tsx         # Shared by ALL instruments
      LessonHeader.tsx
      YouTubeLink.tsx
      NotationSlot.tsx        # Slot filled by instrument plugin at runtime
    course/
      LessonRow.tsx
      CourseHeader.tsx
  hooks/
    useLesson.ts
    useCourse.ts
    useProgress.ts
    useInstrumentPlugin.ts    # Loads plugin from registry by slug
  services/
    apiClient.ts              # Base fetch/axios wrapper
    courses.ts
    lessons.ts
    progress.ts
    auth.ts
  types/
    models.ts                 # Instrument, Level, Course, Lesson, Progress
    api.ts                    # API request/response shapes
    index.ts                  # Re-exports all types
  constants/
    instruments.ts
    levels.ts
    routes.ts
  store/
    authStore.ts              # Zustand: current user, roles, active role
    playerStore.ts            # Zustand: active lesson, playback state, BPM
    progressStore.ts          # Zustand: cached progress
  utils/
    time.ts
    slugs.ts
    roles.ts
```

## Architecture Rules — NEVER violate these

1. `app/` screens contain ZERO business logic. They import from `src/` only.
2. Core screens NEVER import directly from `instruments/harmonium/` or any specific instrument folder.
3. The lesson shell (`app/lesson/[id].tsx`) loads instrument UI exclusively via `useInstrumentPlugin()` hook.
4. Instrument plugins NEVER import from other instrument plugin folders.
5. Instrument plugins CAN import from `src/components/`, `src/hooks/`, `src/utils/`, `src/types/`.
6. Adding a new instrument = new folder in `instruments/` + one line in `instrumentRegistry.ts`. Nothing else changes.
7. All media URLs come from FastAPI signed URL responses — never hardcode R2 bucket paths.
8. `notation.json` format is instrument-specific — each plugin's `parseNotation()` handles its own format.

## User Roles
Roles are stored in PostgreSQL `users.roles` (text array). NOT in Clerk JWT claims.
Roles: learner (default) | tutor | contributor | admin | power_admin
A user can hold multiple roles. Active role is toggled in UI and stored in `authStore`.
Role checks use `src/utils/roles.ts` helper functions — never inline string comparisons.

## TypeScript Rules
- Strict mode enabled — no `any` types
- All API responses typed via `src/types/api.ts`
- All domain models typed via `src/types/models.ts`
- Use `type` not `interface` for data shapes (use `interface` only for plugin contracts)
- Never use `as` casting unless absolutely unavoidable — prefer type guards

## Component Rules
- Functional components only — no class components
- Every component has explicit prop types defined above the component
- No inline styles — always use `StyleSheet.create()` at the bottom of the file
- Loading / error / empty states always handled — never assume data exists
- No `console.log` in committed code — use a proper logger utility

## FastAPI Rules
- All endpoints return typed Pydantic response models
- Auth-protected endpoints use `get_current_user` dependency
- Role-protected endpoints use `require_role("tutor")` style dependency
- Database access via async SQLAlchemy — no raw psycopg2 in routes
- Redis caching on all list endpoints (instruments, levels, courses, lessons)
- Never return raw DB model objects — always map to Pydantic response schemas

## API Conventions
- REST — no GraphQL
- All IDs are UUIDs
- All timestamps are ISO 8601 UTC
- Slugs are lowercase, hyphenated, URL-safe
- Pagination on all list endpoints: `?page=1&limit=20`
- Error responses: `{ "error": { "code": "NOT_FOUND", "message": "..." } }`

## Naming Conventions
- Files: PascalCase for components (`LessonRow.tsx`), camelCase for everything else
- Hooks: always prefixed `use` (`useLesson`, `useCourse`)
- Store files: suffixed `Store` (`authStore`, `playerStore`)
- API service files: domain noun (`courses.ts`, `lessons.ts`)
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE for values, camelCase for the exported object

## What NOT to do
- Do NOT use NativeWind, Tailwind, or CSS-in-JS
- Do NOT use Redux or MobX — Zustand only
- Do NOT use React Navigation manually — Expo Router handles all navigation
- Do NOT put API calls directly in screen components — always go through `src/services/`
- Do NOT use `useEffect` for data fetching — use custom hooks in `src/hooks/`
- Do NOT store auth tokens manually — Clerk handles all token storage
- Do NOT expose R2 bucket names or keys in the frontend
- Do NOT add new instruments by modifying core screens — plugin registry only
